TomatoHub Sprint Context

Completed in this sprint
- Frontend public campaign list and campaign detail now load from backend API instead of `frontend/mocks`.
- Frontend home page featured campaigns now load from backend API.
- Organization dashboard and supporter dashboard now load live metrics from backend endpoints.
- Organization create campaign page now submits a real draft campaign to backend with authenticated organization token.
- Frontend now has a shared API layer in `frontend/lib/api/*` and normalized domain types for campaigns and dashboards.
- Auth context now exposes `accessToken` so protected client pages can call backend without reading localStorage in many places.
- Frontend auth/user types are now centralized in `frontend/types/user.ts`; `frontend/lib/auth/types.ts` re-exports those shared types instead of drifting separately.
- Supporter signup is now a 2-step flow:
  - Step 1 at `frontend/app/(public)/signup/supporter/page.tsx` collects account info.
  - Step 2 at `frontend/app/(public)/signup/supporter/support-types/page.tsx` collects optional support preferences and finishes signup.
  - Temporary signup state is kept in `frontend/lib/auth/SupporterSignupFlowContext.tsx`.
- User-facing dashboard/profile pages now use `frontend/components/auth/RoleGate.tsx` so supporter and organization routes do not render the wrong account state while auth is restoring.
- Dashboard backend endpoints are now authenticated for the logged-in account:
  - Supporters can only view their own dashboard.
  - Organizations can only view their own dashboard.
- Frontend dashboard workspaces for `/supporter` and `/organization` were refreshed visually with improved sidebars, hero sections, and activity panels.
- Sample frontend-only engagement data now exists in `frontend/mocks/dashboard-experience.ts` to support UI work for:
  - supporter joined campaigns
  - supporter contribution history
  - supporter task states
  - organization campaign pipeline cards
  - organization recent activity feed
- Backend write authorization is tighter:
  - `POST/PATCH /campaigns` and `POST /campaigns/{id}/publish` require organization ownership.
  - `POST /donations` cannot spoof `donor_user_id`; linked donations require authenticated matching user.
  - `POST /volunteer-registrations` cannot spoof `user_id`; linked registrations require authenticated matching user and always start as `pending`.
  - `POST /organizations` now requires superuser.
- Repo hygiene improved with `.gitignore` updates and minimal permission tests added in `backend/tests/test_permissions.py`.

